==Changes==
{{Subject changes header}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 28 February 2024
|update = Defender of Varrock Artwork & QoL Updates
|change = 
* Players can now toggle off the cooldown timer in the [[Steam Client]].
* Items dropped in public rooms now disappear after three minutes.
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 7 February 2024
|update = Poll 80 Wilderness Changes & More
|change = 
* Scurrius now properly appears in alphabetical order in the [[Collection Log]] interface, rather than being above Sarachnis.
* [[Group Ironman Mode|Group Ironmen]] can now enter Scurrius' lair together through a shared [[instance]].
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 31 January 2024
|update = Scurrius & DT2 Combat Achievements
|change = 
* Scurrius now counts towards [[Slayer task/Rats|rat Slayer tasks]].
* [[Combat Achievements]] were added for the boss.
* Scurrius now drops medium clue scrolls for the player who dealt the most damage at a rate of 1/25.
* Any [[big bones]] and [[rat meat]] left on the floor in the private instance will now disappear after the normal 2.5 minutes used outside [[instance]]s. Other loot is left unchanged, remaining on the ground for much longer.
}}
{{Subject changes footer}}

==Trivia ==
* A {{WP|rat king}} is a collection of rats whose tails are intertwined and bound together in some way.
*The examine text refers to the myth that rats are always present in urban areas, even if the person doesn't see them.
* Scurrius was originally conceived as a concept from the [[April 2023 Game Jam#The_Rat_King_(Free-to-play_mechanics-based_boss)|April 2023 Game Jam]].
* Unlike most large monsters, Scurrius drops its loot on the centre of the 3x3 tiles it occupies, rather than its south-westernmost tile. [[Long bone]]s,  [[curved bone]]s, and [[Clue scroll (medium)|medium clues]] are dropped on the south-westernmost tile, however.
* It was hinted at during the 26 January 2024 Old School Live stream that one of the smaller rats is actually in control of Scurrius, presumably the mage head is in control of Scurrius itself.

